&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a highly motivated and dynamic individual to join the Procurement team at London North West University Healthcare NHS Trust. The successful applicant will be responsible for:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• procurement data creation, business reporting and commercial analysis, &lt;br /&gt;• assisting project management and &lt;br /&gt;• providing information to assist in creating savings, spend analysis, operational and strategic planning. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will work closely administratively supporting the Procurement Management Team to run projects and assist development and production of useful commercial information and spend analysis for procurement audit and spend/supplier research purposes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will support Ecommerce systems and be a driver of commercial modernization.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Ideally you should be educated to degree level or equivalent, in IT, Economics, Procurement, Business or Informatics or equivalent relevant high experience &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You need to:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• Possess skills in the use of critical analysis and initiative, in the resolution of problems and development of service models&lt;br /&gt;• Have good communication, team-working and presentation skills &lt;br /&gt;• Have a general understanding of procurement and its role in the NHS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If this sounds like you please apply and give evidenced details of what you have done and what you can do for us as part of developing a best practice team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMr Carl MorleseJob titleInterim Head of ProcurementEmail addresscarl.morlese@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
